qas.question: Where did the capital move to after the reign of Guangwu?
What era does the reign of Guangwu fall under?
What can the Eastern Han dynasty also be called?
Where was the capital located during the Western Han dynasty?
What can the Western Han dynasty also be called?

context: The period between the foundation of the Han dynasty and Wang Mang's reign is known as the Western Han dynasty (simplified Chinese: 西汉; traditional Chinese: 西漢; pinyin: Xī Hàn) or <a4_0>Former Han dynasty<a4_0/> (simplified Chinese: 前汉; traditional Chinese: 前漢; pinyin: Qiánhàn) (206 BC – 9 AD). During this period the capital was at <a3_0>Chang'an<a3_0/> (modern Xi'an). From the reign of Guangwu the capital was moved eastward to <a0_0>Luoyang<a0_0/>. The era from his reign until the fall of Han is known as the <a1_0>Eastern Han dynasty<a1_0/> (simplified Chinese: 东汉; traditional Chinese: 東漢; pinyin: Dōng Hàn) or the <a2_0>Later Han dynasty<a2_0/> (simplified Chinese: 后汉; traditional Chinese: 後漢; pinyin: Hòu Hàn) (25–220 AD).
